## Problema 5 <a name="5"></a>
**Enunciado:**
Medir
coeficiente
$$\theta$$
con:
$$P = I \cdot V = \theta(T_d - T_a)$$
Datos:
$$I = 25.23 \pm 0.04$$
$$\text{mA}$$
$$V = 5.234 \pm 0.002$$
$$\text{V}$$
$$T_a = 25.2 \pm 0.5$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
$$T_d = 67.2 \pm 1.5$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
Cálculo de
$$\theta$$
y su
incertidumbre.

**Solución:**
1. Fórmula:
$$\theta = \frac{I \cdot V}{T_d - T_a}$$

2. Valor medio:
$$\theta = \frac{25.23 \times 10^{-3} \cdot 5.234}{67.2 - 25.2}$$
$$\theta = \frac{0.13205382}{42}$$
$$\theta = 0.003144$$
$$\text{W/}^{\circ}\text{C}$$
$$\theta = 3.144$$
$$\text{mW/}^{\circ}\text{C}$$

3. Incertidum-
bre
Derivadas:
- Corriente
$$\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial I} = \frac{V}{T_d - T_a}$$
$$\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial I} = 0.1246$$
Aportación:
$$u_I = 0.1246 \cdot 0.04$$
$$u_I = 0.00498$$
- Tensión
$$\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial V} = \frac{I}{T_d - T_a}$$
$$\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial V} = 0.6007$$
Aportación:
$$u_V = 0.6007 \cdot 0.002$$
$$u_V = 0.00120$$
- Temp Td
$$\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial T_d} = -\frac{I \cdot V}{(T_d - T_a)^2}$$
$$\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial T_d} = -0.07486$$
Aportación:
$$u_{Td} = -0.07486 \cdot 1.5$$
$$u_{Td} = -0.11229$$
- Temp Ta
$$\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial T_a} = \frac{I \cdot V}{(T_d - T_a)^2}$$
$$\frac{\partial \theta}{\partial T_a} = 0.07486$$
Aportación:
$$u_{Ta} = 0.07486 \cdot 0.5$$
$$u_{Ta} = 0.03743$$

Suma de
cuadrados:
$$U_\theta^2 = u_I^2 + u_V^2 + u_{Td}^2 + u_{Ta}^2$$
$$U_\theta^2 = 0.00498^2 + 0.00120^2 + (-0.11229)^2 + 0.03743^2$$
$$U_\theta^2 = 0.000025 + 0.000001 + 0.012609 + 0.001401$$
$$U_\theta^2 = 0.014036$$
Desviación:
$$U_\theta = 0.1185 \approx 0.13$$
$$\text{mW/}^{\circ}\text{C}$$

Resultado:
$$\theta = 3.14 \pm 0.13$$
$$\text{mW/}^{\circ}\text{C}$$

