## Problema 6 <a name="6"></a>
**Enunciado:**
Potencia
motor:
$$P = F \cdot l \cdot 2\pi \cdot \frac{\theta}{t}$$
Datos:
$$F = 983 \pm 2$$
$$\text{N}$$
$$l = 30.02 \pm 0.01$$
$$\text{cm}$$
$$\theta = 520.02 \pm 0.07$$
$$\text{rev}$$
$$t = 50.02 \pm 0.015$$
$$\text{s}$$
Calcular
potencia e
incertidumbre.

**Solución:**
1. Conversión:
$$l = 0.3002 \pm 0.0001$$
$$\text{m}$$
$$\theta = 520.02 \cdot 2\pi$$
$$\text{rad}$$
Portanto
$$P = F \cdot l \cdot \omega$$
donde:
$$\omega = \frac{\theta \cdot 2\pi}{t}$$
$$\omega = \frac{520.02 \cdot 2\pi}{50.02}$$
$$\omega \approx 65.318$$
$$\text{rad/s}$$

2. Valor medio:
$$P = 983 \cdot 0.3002 \cdot 65.318$$
$$P = 19275.25$$
$$\text{W}$$

3. Incertidum-
bre
Aportación
relativa de
cada término:
- Fuerza
$$\frac{u_F}{F} = \frac{2}{983} = 0.00203$$
- Longitud
$$\frac{u_l}{l} = \frac{0.01}{30.02} = 0.00033$$
- Vueltas
$$\frac{u_\theta}{\theta} = \frac{0.07}{520.02} = 0.00013$$
- Tiempo
$$\frac{u_t}{t} = \frac{0.015}{50.02} = 0.00030$$

Incertidumbre
relativa de
potencia:
$$\frac{u_P}{P} = \sqrt{ \left(\frac{u_F}{F}\right)^2 + \left(\frac{u_l}{l}\right)^2 + \left(\frac{u_\theta}{\theta}\right)^2 + \left(\frac{u_t}{t}\right)^2 }$$
$$\frac{u_P}{P} = \sqrt{ 0.00203^2 + 0.00033^2 + 0.00013^2 + 0.00030^2 }$$
$$\frac{u_P}{P} = \sqrt{ 4.12 \times 10^{-6} + 1.09 \times 10^{-7} + 1.69 \times 10^{-8} + 9 \times 10^{-8} }$$
$$\frac{u_P}{P} = \sqrt{ 4.33 \times 10^{-6} }$$
$$\frac{u_P}{P} = 0.00208$$

Incertidumbre
absoluta:
$$u_P = 19275.25 \cdot 0.00208$$
$$u_P \approx 40.1$$
$$\text{W}$$

Redondeo:
$$P = (19.28 \pm 0.04) \times 10^3$$
$$\text{W}$$
o:
$$P = 19280 \pm 40$$
$$\text{W}$$
